---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base
  title="Advertising Disclosure | The Life Insider"
  description="How The Life Insider makes money, how compensation affects what we feature, and what never changes: our scores are built from real customer review data."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container-narrow prose">
      <h1>Advertising Disclosure</h1>
      <p class="updated">Last updated: July 2026</p>

      <p class="lede">
        We believe you deserve to know exactly how this site makes money
        before you rely on our recommendations. Here it is, in plain English.
      </p>

      <h2>We earn affiliate commissions</h2>
      <p>
        The Life Insider is a review and comparison publication. When you
        click a link on our site and make a purchase from a retailer or brand,
        we may receive an affiliate commission from that retailer or brand.
        This never increases the price you pay.
      </p>
      <p>
        As an Amazon Associate, The Life Insider earns from qualifying
        purchases.
      </p>

      <h2>How compensation affects our content</h2>
      <p>Honestly and specifically:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>It influences which products and categories we cover.</strong>
          We generally feature products for which an affiliate or advertising
          relationship exists — that's how the research gets funded.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>It can influence placement and ordering</strong> among
          products of comparable quality. Where two products earn similar
          Insider Scores, a product from a partner brand may be featured more
          prominently.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>It never changes a product's underlying score.</strong> The
          Insider Score is calculated from verified customer review data,
          review volume, value analysis, and brand reliability, as described
          in <a href="/how-we-rate/">How We Rate</a>. We do not sell score
          points, and we will not rank a product #1 that the data doesn't
          support as a genuinely excellent choice.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>We are not the seller</h2>
      <p>
        We do not manufacture, sell, ship, or warranty any product featured on
        this site. All purchases are made from and fulfilled by the linked
        retailer or brand, under their prices, terms, returns policies, and
        guarantees. Always review the seller's terms before purchasing.
      </p>

      <h2>Pricing and offers</h2>
      <p>
        Prices, discounts, and availability change frequently and are
        controlled by retailers — not by us. Any price or discount shown on
        our site reflects the information available at the time of our last
        update and may have changed. Click through to the retailer for the
        current price.
      </p>

      <h2>Sponsored content</h2>
      <p>
        If a piece of content is directly sponsored by a brand, it will be
        clearly labeled as such on the page. Our standard review pages are not
        written or approved by the brands featured in them.
      </p>

      <h2>Questions?</h2>
      <p>
        We're happy to explain further — <a href="/contact/">contact us here</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
